♪ And mine, <i>Happy Days!</i> ♪

01:17.044 --> 01:20.844
Happy Days is <i>filmed</i>
before a studio audience.

01:22.683 --> 01:24.913
JOANIE: AI, we've been
practicing our cheers all week.

01:25.052 --> 01:26.417
<i>What do you think of this?</i>

01:26.553 --> 01:29.215
Jefferson,
Jefferson, Jefferson High,

01:29.356 --> 01:31.916
You can beat this team,
don't settle for a tie.

01:32.059 --> 01:34.118
You got them on the run,
you got them in a spin,

01:34.261 --> 01:36.457
so grab that ball
and win, win, win!

01:36.597 --> 01:38.793
(cheering)

01:38.932 --> 01:41.230
(whooping)

01:49.843 --> 01:52.141
You're all too kind.

01:52.279 --> 01:53.644
Hi, Fonz.
Uh, bye, Fonz.

01:53.780 --> 01:55.680
The game starts in two hours.

01:55.816 --> 01:58.649
- Oh, yeah!
- We barely have time to flirt.

02:00.921 --> 02:03.947
Hey, uh, Al, listen,
I got a ten-minute lunch.

02:04.091 --> 02:07.186
Yeah, I'm tuning up
a bookmobile. Very stacked.

02:07.327 --> 02:10.627
- Lots of books?
- Lots of librarians.

02:10.764 --> 02:14.291
What you need is
my famous hit-and-run special.

02:14.434 --> 02:17.233
Clarence!
Give me a hit, hit, hit...

02:17.371 --> 02:20.363
Al. Run, run, run, run.

02:21.642 --> 02:24.168
(quietly):
Jefferson, Jefferson...

02:24.311 --> 02:26.177
Here you go, Fonz.
Bon appetit.

02:26.313 --> 02:28.782
There is no parsley
on this plate.

02:28.915 --> 02:31.213
Oh, I'm-I'm sorry. I forgot.

02:31.351 --> 02:33.115
And, uh, not the canned kind.

02:33.253 --> 02:35.745
My body needs fresh.

02:35.889 --> 02:38.483
- Here you go, Fonz.
- Thank you.

02:38.625 --> 02:39.888
Why do you eat that stuff?

02:40.027 --> 02:42.496
Why does Popeye eat spinach?

02:42.629 --> 02:45.621
- Let me try one.
- Go right ahead.

02:46.967 --> 02:48.594
AL:
Mm. I'll stick to spinach.

02:48.735 --> 02:50.897
Al, I got great news.

02:52.906 --> 02:54.431
Fonz...

02:54.574 --> 02:56.975
uh... Fonz,
I have got the greatest news.

02:57.110 --> 02:58.976
I got a ten-minute lunch.
Talk fast.

02:59.112 --> 03:01.171
Oh, sure. Oh, parsley. Hey.

03:01.314 --> 03:03.840
Fonz, I got a job.

03:03.984 --> 03:05.076
On a newspaper.

03:05.218 --> 03:07.050
<i>Milwaukee Shoppers News.</i>

03:07.187 --> 03:08.518
Hey, that's terrific.
You gonna write up front,

03:08.655 --> 03:10.214
like on the front page
or something like that?

03:10.357 --> 03:12.826
Well, uh,
a-a little further back.

03:12.959 --> 03:14.688
The obituaries?

03:14.828 --> 03:16.728
Not that, no.

03:16.863 --> 03:18.558
It's gonna be great experience.

03:18.699 --> 03:19.598
They're not paying you, huh?

03:19.733 --> 03:21.258
Well, no.

03:21.401 --> 03:23.233
But, Fonz, a lot of people
are gonna read it,

03:23.370 --> 03:24.997
and it could lead
to bigger things for me.

03:25.138 --> 03:26.799
It's sort of an advice column.

03:26.940 --> 03:28.032
What kind?

03:28.175 --> 03:29.074
"Ask Aunt Fanny."

03:29.209 --> 03:30.301
I'm asking you.

03:30.444 --> 03:32.708
No, that's what it is, Fonz.

03:32.846 --> 03:34.814
It's an advice-
to-the-lovelorn column.

03:34.948 --> 03:35.813
I knew that.

03:35.949 --> 03:37.940
And I'm, uh...

03:40.520 --> 03:42.921
I'm Aunt Fanny.

03:44.291 --> 03:46.157
- No...
- Yeah.

03:46.293 --> 03:47.658
Well, it's just for two weeks.

03:47.794 --> 03:49.819
Aunt Fanny's in Mexico
getting a divorce.

03:51.765 --> 03:54.063
Uncle Fanny got caught cheating?

03:54.201 --> 03:55.430
(chuckles):
Yeah.

03:55.569 --> 03:57.435
This is really
my big break, Fonz. I mean...

03:57.571 --> 03:59.437
Well, you see,
if I could impress the editor,

03:59.573 --> 04:01.871
then I'd probably get
a column of my own, you know,

04:02.008 --> 04:05.205
and then I'd go syndicated...
and my own TV show.

04:05.345 --> 04:07.814
Who knows?
It happened to Ed Sullivan.

04:07.948 --> 04:09.814
(like Ed Sullivan):
This is Richie Cunningham.

04:09.950 --> 04:11.816
Right here on our stage tonight

04:11.952 --> 04:15.616
we have the entire population
of Belgium with their pets.

04:15.756 --> 04:18.281
Sit down, Mr. Broadway.

04:18.425 --> 04:20.189
- When do you start?
- Well, I already started.

04:20.327 --> 04:21.589
I've already done
my first column.

04:21.728 --> 04:24.823
Matter of fact,
listen to this, Fonz.

04:24.965 --> 04:27.627
"Dear Aunt Fanny..."
- Yeah, that's good.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.202
RICHIE:
There's more.

04:29.336 --> 04:31.134
"...my husband likes
to show off at parties

04:31.271 --> 04:33.035
by eating dog biscuits..."

04:34.207 --> 04:36.198
That saves
on the hors d'oeuvres.

04:36.343 --> 04:38.903
Yeah, well,
that's not the problem.

04:39.045 --> 04:42.379
"Now, I know dog biscuits aren't
good for him, but what can I do?

04:42.516 --> 04:44.507
Signed, Concerned Wife."

04:44.651 --> 04:46.244
- What'd you tell him?
- Mm.

04:47.888 --> 04:51.381
"If you want a happy marriage,
let your husband have his fun.

04:51.525 --> 04:55.120
And check him for fleas
once a month."

04:56.797 --> 04:58.788
Here's another one.

05:01.468 --> 05:02.663
"Dear Aunt Fanny,

05:02.803 --> 05:04.669
"I'm an attractive girl of 18,

05:04.805 --> 05:06.864
"but haven't had
a lot of dating experience.

05:07.007 --> 05:08.236
"What can I do?

05:08.375 --> 05:10.673
Signed, Puckered but Depressed."

05:10.811 --> 05:13.678
I'll handle that one.

05:13.814 --> 05:15.213
Well, that's, uh...

05:15.348 --> 05:18.010
yeah, that's more or less
the advice I gave her.

05:18.151 --> 05:19.346
Fonz, one favor.

05:19.486 --> 05:21.147
Don't tell anybody, okay?

05:21.288 --> 05:23.655
Humble. I love humble!

05:23.790 --> 05:25.280
Yeah, I'm-I'm humble.

05:25.425 --> 05:26.984
That, and, uh...

05:27.127 --> 05:29.391
Aunt Fanny told me she'd fire me
if I said anything.

05:29.529 --> 05:31.224
- FONZIE: I understand.
- Yeah.

05:31.364 --> 05:33.298
Oh, I got to phone in
my deadline.

05:33.433 --> 05:34.696
That's newspaper talk.

05:34.835 --> 05:37.065
Fonz, would you mind if I use
the phone in your office?

05:37.204 --> 05:39.639
- Knock yourself out.
- Great. Thanks a lot.

05:41.041 --> 05:43.339
All right, all right.

05:43.476 --> 05:45.467
All right, Malph...

05:47.047 --> 05:48.572
Okay, Malph.

05:48.715 --> 05:50.046
All right, if you're
not gonna make lunch,

05:50.183 --> 05:51.582
I'm gonna eat here.
It was your turn!

05:51.718 --> 05:53.846
I couldn't fix lunch-- I was
looking for the showerhead!

05:53.987 --> 05:55.955
Ah. You mean this thing?

05:56.990 --> 05:58.355
- You had it!
- Yeah.

05:58.491 --> 05:59.720
All right, hand it over, Pots.

05:59.860 --> 06:01.988
- Not until you give me back
my lava lamp. -Forget it.

06:02.128 --> 06:04.597
- I'll just go home and take
a nice long bath. -Oh, yeah?

06:04.731 --> 06:06.426
- Without water?
-(laughs)

06:06.566 --> 06:07.727
No problem.

06:07.868 --> 06:09.632
I'll just stuff the drain
with your new shirt.

06:09.769 --> 06:10.998
You better not touch
my new shirt, Malph.

06:11.137 --> 06:12.104
The pants are going in, too.

06:12.239 --> 06:13.434
Oh, I'd like to see you
get my pants.

06:13.573 --> 06:14.699
- Oh, come on, Pots...
- Who do you think you are...?

06:14.841 --> 06:17.139
Hold it! You guys are terrible
for the digestion.

06:17.277 --> 06:18.745
What is this, a slumber party?

06:18.879 --> 06:21.211
No, Fonz, we're fighting again.

06:21.348 --> 06:22.406
Always. You're always fighting.

06:22.549 --> 06:24.039
Not always.
Just when we're together.

06:25.719 --> 06:27.153
- We need a referee.
- Yeah.

06:27.287 --> 06:29.517
- What am I wearing, a striped
shirt and a whistle? -Aw, Fonz,

06:29.656 --> 06:31.283
we got to talk to somebody--
we need advice.

06:31.424 --> 06:32.892
- Expert advice.
We need an expert. -Yeah.

06:33.026 --> 06:33.993
- You need an expert?
- Yeah.

06:34.127 --> 06:36.960
- I know an expert.
- You do? -Who?

06:37.097 --> 06:39.498
Why don't you...
ask Aunt Fanny?

06:39.633 --> 06:41.260
(chuckles)

06:44.471 --> 06:48.169
<i>JOANIE: Why do I have to wear
one of Fat Phyllis's dresses?</i>

06:48.308 --> 06:51.175
<i>MARION: Dear,
your cousin Phyllis is not fat.</i>

06:51.311 --> 06:53.405
Anyway, when I get this
cut down, you're gonna have

06:53.546 --> 06:56.140
a new dress and I'm gonna have a
set of kitchen curtains.

06:56.283 --> 06:59.651
But, Mom, everyone will know
this is her dress.

06:59.786 --> 07:02.619
No, they won't, dear.

07:02.756 --> 07:04.087
JOANIE:
It'll look like a tent.

07:04.224 --> 07:08.058
There's a, uh, a bookmobile
parked in the driveway.

07:09.229 --> 07:10.754
Oh, that's nice, dear.

07:10.897 --> 07:13.195
Did you have a nice day
at school?

07:13.333 --> 07:16.064
Mom, college is not school.

07:16.202 --> 07:18.432
Fat Phyllis's dress, huh?

07:18.571 --> 07:20.198
Mom...

07:23.043 --> 07:25.705
- Daddy's home! Yeah.
- Hi, Dad.

07:25.845 --> 07:27.540
I hope you're satisfied, Marion.

07:27.681 --> 07:29.547
You have made me
the laughingstock

07:29.683 --> 07:31.811
-of the whole neighborhood.
- Heh! Not for long.

07:31.952 --> 07:34.182
Wait until they get a load
of this dress.

07:34.321 --> 07:35.686
Well, what's wrong, Howard?

07:35.822 --> 07:37.517
What's wrong?
I'll tell you what's wrong.

07:37.657 --> 07:39.386
It's the letter you wrote
to Aunt Fanny!

07:39.526 --> 07:41.494
- You wrote a letter
to Aunt Fanny? -HOWARD: Yeah.

07:41.628 --> 07:43.653
No, she wouldn't write a letter
to Aunt Fanny.

07:43.797 --> 07:46.095
Oh, no? Well,
you just listen to this.

07:46.232 --> 07:48.200
"Dear Aunt Fanny,

07:48.335 --> 07:51.032
"my husband is supposed
to be on a diet,

07:51.171 --> 07:54.334
"but he hides Tootsie Rolls
in his cash register

07:54.474 --> 07:58.035
"and tells everyone
they're rolls of dirty nickels.

07:59.579 --> 08:02.378
"What can I do
to keep him on his diet?

08:02.515 --> 08:03.778
"Signed...

08:03.917 --> 08:05.681
Wife of Chubbo."

08:05.819 --> 08:07.412
Ooh!

08:07.554 --> 08:10.546
Sure caught you, Mom--
there it is in black and white.

08:10.690 --> 08:13.159
- Howard, I didn't write
that letter. -You didn't?

08:13.293 --> 08:14.590
No, of course not.

08:14.728 --> 08:17.163
Ah. She didn't write a letter
to Aunt Fanny. Heh.

08:17.297 --> 08:19.288
Well, everyone at the store
thinks she did.

08:19.432 --> 08:21.298
I mean, when I left,
they were singing,

08:21.434 --> 08:24.597
♪ Toot-Toot-Tootsie,
good-bye... ♪

08:24.738 --> 08:27.105
Oh! Oh, that's a good one,
that really is.

08:27.240 --> 08:29.641
No, that's... that's
not a good one, Marion.

08:29.776 --> 08:33.337
- Mm. No.
- You, get out of my chair.

08:33.480 --> 08:36.381
Oh, you're wearing
Fat Phyllis's dress.

08:36.515 --> 08:37.984
That's it!
That's it, Mom.

08:38.118 --> 08:41.349
You can make yourself
two sets of curtains.

08:41.488 --> 08:44.082
Howard, what am
I gonna do with her?

08:44.224 --> 08:46.192
Maybe you should write a letter
to <i>Aunt</i> Fanny.

08:46.326 --> 08:48.727
Aunt Fanny is full of malarkey.

08:48.862 --> 08:52.127
Dear, she's somebody's aunt--
she must know something.

08:53.500 --> 08:56.663
Well, I'm gonna go and fix
Fat Phyllis's dress now.

08:56.803 --> 08:58.328
Dad, I've read that column,

08:58.471 --> 09:00.496
and I think she gives
very sound advice.

09:00.640 --> 09:01.801
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

09:01.941 --> 09:03.534
Well, just listen to this one.

09:03.676 --> 09:07.442
"Dear Aunt Fanny, we used
to get along just great,

09:07.580 --> 09:10.413
"but now we fight all the time.

09:10.550 --> 09:13.576
"We try to respect
each other's rights,

09:13.720 --> 09:17.554
"but it's very hard to know
where to draw the line.

09:17.690 --> 09:20.318
Signed, Troubled Twosome."

09:22.328 --> 09:25.923
Now, there is a young couple
that desperately needs help.

09:26.066 --> 09:27.932
I think you'll find that answer
very helpful.

09:28.068 --> 09:31.663
Helpful? It's frivolous.
It could do more harm than good.

09:31.805 --> 09:33.705
<i>POTSIE: I made the dinner.
It's your turn to clean up.</i>

09:33.840 --> 09:34.705
<i>- RALPH: Isn't.
- Is.</i>

09:34.841 --> 09:35.706
<i>Isn't!</i>

09:35.842 --> 09:37.071
So we agreed that Aunt Fanny's

09:37.210 --> 09:38.837
-gonna settle this thing
for us, right? -Right.

09:38.978 --> 09:42.414
Okay, then let's call a truce
until we read what she says.

09:42.549 --> 09:44.643
- All right. A truce
in five seconds. -All right.

09:44.784 --> 09:46.479
- Five, four...
- Three, two...

09:46.619 --> 09:48.018
Do you always have
to interrupt me, Malph?

09:48.154 --> 09:50.145
- Is the truce on or isn't it?!
- One. Truce is on!

09:50.290 --> 09:51.883
All right, no more yelling,
no more getting excited

09:52.025 --> 09:53.424
-till we hear from Aunt Fanny,
right? -Right!

09:53.560 --> 09:55.551
- All right!
- All right.

10:00.733 --> 10:02.599
I think I'll clean up, Pots.

10:02.735 --> 10:04.760
I mean, you made the din-din.

10:04.904 --> 10:06.429
Thank you, Malph.

10:06.573 --> 10:08.564
You're welcome.

10:15.115 --> 10:17.049
I really appreciate
your thoughtfulness.

10:17.183 --> 10:19.208
And I appreciate
your appreciation

10:19.352 --> 10:21.343
of my thoughtfulness.

10:21.488 --> 10:24.185
Why, thank you.
I really appreciate that.

10:24.324 --> 10:26.315
See that, Potsie?
See how nice it is

10:26.459 --> 10:30.293
when two people can carry on
an adult conversation like this.

10:30.430 --> 10:31.920
It certainly is.

10:32.065 --> 10:33.362
And may I also add

10:33.500 --> 10:35.832
that you certainly are a whiz
in the kitchen.

10:35.969 --> 10:38.097
Oh, thank you kindly.

10:38.238 --> 10:39.535
What was that vegetable
you served?

10:39.672 --> 10:40.935
Refried beets.

10:41.074 --> 10:43.168
Yum, yum, yum.

10:43.309 --> 10:44.674
Yeah.

10:44.811 --> 10:47.007
And I love
your pork chops, Chef.

10:47.147 --> 10:48.478
Oh, a very special recipe.

10:48.615 --> 10:50.310
Pork chops
stuffed with peanuts.

10:50.450 --> 10:52.509
Great, great, just great.

10:52.652 --> 10:54.177
- Yeah. -I would have
preferred them shelled,

10:54.320 --> 10:56.516
-but who's complaining?
-(knocking)

10:56.656 --> 10:57.589
Oh, I'll get it.

10:57.724 --> 10:59.192
No, I'll get it, Pots.
You relax.

10:59.325 --> 11:01.726
Why, thank you, Malph.

11:01.861 --> 11:03.659
Huh.

11:03.796 --> 11:06.288
- Chachi!
- Hey, Ralph. Hey, Pots.

11:06.432 --> 11:08.924
_l-low you doing?
_l-low you doing...?

11:09.068 --> 11:11.662
You guys are hitting each other
with pots now, huh?

11:11.804 --> 11:14.330
No, no. I haven't hit Pots
with a pot all week.

11:14.474 --> 11:15.566
Yeah, good one, that's good.

11:15.708 --> 11:17.699
Yeah, even in a truce I got it.

11:17.844 --> 11:19.710
That's right, Chach,
we called a truce

11:19.846 --> 11:21.712
till we get professional help.

11:21.848 --> 11:23.441
Hey, that's great.
Oh, by the way,

11:23.583 --> 11:25.677
my mother sent me down
to collect the rent.

11:25.818 --> 11:28.981
And, look, this time she
doesn't want it all in pennies.

11:29.122 --> 11:30.419
(Ralph chuckles)

11:30.557 --> 11:32.992
She have something
against Lincoln?

11:33.126 --> 11:35.185
- Here you go. -Thanks, guys.
I'll see you later.

11:35.328 --> 11:37.126
- RALPHIPOTSIE: All right.
- Oh. Almost forgot.

11:37.263 --> 11:38.253
I brought your mail.

11:38.398 --> 11:39.559
- Oh, thanks, Chach.
- Oh, great.

11:39.699 --> 11:41.929
- I have this real heavy date,
you know? -Mm-hmm.

11:42.068 --> 11:43.866
But I took the time because...

11:44.003 --> 11:45.562
well, you guys are worth it.

11:45.705 --> 11:46.570
No tip, Chach.

11:46.706 --> 11:47.935
It's probably bills.

11:48.074 --> 11:50.168
<i>- The Milwaukee Shoppers News.
- Oh, give it over here.</i>

11:50.310 --> 11:51.744
Not so fast, Pots.

11:51.878 --> 11:53.539
This is C.O.D.

11:53.680 --> 11:56.081
And you guys know what
C.0.D. means, don't you?

11:56.216 --> 11:58.810
Yeah. C.O.D.--
Chachi Out Door.

11:58.952 --> 12:01.444
- POTSIE: Right.
- Come on, guys.

12:01.588 --> 12:03.488
- Thanks for the lift.
- Bye.

12:03.623 --> 12:05.648
Come on. We got
our professional advice.

12:05.792 --> 12:07.123
- Okay.
- All right.

12:07.260 --> 12:08.523
Wait a minute, Potsie...

12:08.661 --> 12:10.129
before we read it, remember,

12:10.263 --> 12:12.823
whatever she says
is what we're gonna do. Agreed?

12:12.966 --> 12:13.990
- Ag reed.
- Okay.

12:14.133 --> 12:15.225
All right. Heh.

12:15.368 --> 12:17.735
Here we go.
"Dear Troubled Twosome..."

12:17.870 --> 12:20.669
- Hey, our name's in the paper.
- Just read it, Pots.

12:20.807 --> 12:23.139
"So you don't know
where to draw the line.

12:23.276 --> 12:27.543
Easy. Draw it
down the middle of the room."

12:27.680 --> 12:30.672
Down the middle of the room.

12:30.817 --> 12:32.683
She's absolutely right.

