night's sleep in a week.

15:33.599 --> 15:36.034
Hey, I'm very proud of you, huh?

15:36.169 --> 15:39.230
No, Fonz, you don't understand--
you see, it's Ralph and Potsie.

15:39.372 --> 15:41.466
- Yeah.
- They're fighting again.

15:41.607 --> 15:43.575
Day and night, day and night.

15:43.709 --> 15:45.108
Well, mostly night.

15:45.244 --> 15:47.838
What a misuse of darkness.

15:47.980 --> 15:49.311
No, Fonz,
this time it's serious.

15:49.449 --> 15:51.577
Would you believe these two guys
are talkin' splitsville?

15:51.717 --> 15:53.913
And just because some...
some dummy gave 'em advice?

15:54.053 --> 15:55.452
- What dummy, huh?
- Aunt Fanny.

15:55.588 --> 15:57.056
Uh-oh.

16:01.494 --> 16:03.360
<i>RICHIE:
Mom? What's for dinner?</i>

16:03.496 --> 16:04.964
<i>MARION: It's a <i>surprise.</i></i>

16:05.097 --> 16:07.532
All right, everybody.

16:07.667 --> 16:10.602
Now, this is the appetizer.

16:13.573 --> 16:15.200
Well?

16:15.341 --> 16:16.672
RICHIE:
Interesting, Mom.

16:16.809 --> 16:18.777
Uh... what is it?

16:18.911 --> 16:21.278
I read in "Aunt Fanny"
a wife should serve something

16:21.414 --> 16:22.540
completely different

16:22.682 --> 16:25.014
