Get away from my refrigerator!

18:03.249 --> 18:04.648
Aw, come on, Pots,
give me a break.

18:04.784 --> 18:06.218
I haven't had
anything cold in days.

18:06.352 --> 18:08.150
If I get to use your stove.

18:08.287 --> 18:10.312
- Okay, one stovey.
- All right.

18:10.456 --> 18:12.185
RALPH:
Hey! Hey!

18:12.325 --> 18:14.123
Your leg's on my side
of the tape.

18:14.260 --> 18:15.659
I get a trip
to the bathroom for that.

18:15.795 --> 18:18.264
All right, all right. Just
let me cook my dinner, okay?

18:23.636 --> 18:26.162
It's nice to be back home.

18:26.305 --> 18:27.966
Ha-ha-ha.

18:29.141 --> 18:30.836
Yeah.

18:30.977 --> 18:33.241
Ah-ah-ah, your side of the line.

18:33.379 --> 18:35.541
How am I supposed
to cook my dinner, Malph?

18:35.681 --> 18:38.173
Simple. I'll turn on the oven.

18:38.317 --> 18:40.752
I'll even go so far
as to open the door.

18:40.886 --> 18:42.354
Oh, heat.
It's warm already.

18:42.488 --> 18:43.853
All yours, Pots.

18:43.990 --> 18:45.355
What am I supposed to do,
throw it?

18:45.491 --> 18:46.686
Unless you want to mail it.

18:53.065 --> 18:54.692
Oh, look! Look!

18:54.834 --> 18:58.998
I found a TV dinner
on my side of the room.

18:59.138 --> 19:01.197
You give me that dinner back,
Malph, right now!

19:01.340 --> 19:03.206
-(phone ringing)
- You give me that dinner back.

19:03.342 --> 19:04.810
Ah. Ah...

19:04.944 --> 19:08.141
My side, my phone, my slop,

19:08.280 --> 19:11.375
my books, my pictures, my phone.

19:11.517 --> 19:13.952
Hello. Ralph Malph's
side of the room.

19:14.086 --> 19:15.611
Mm-hmm. Yes.

19:15.755 --> 19:17.723
Of course.
It's for you, Pots.

19:17.857 --> 19:18.790
Big deal.

19:18.924 --> 19:20.949
Does she sound gorgeous!

19:21.093 --> 19:22.492
Great! Great!

19:22.628 --> 19:24.460
Uh-uh-uh. Uh-uh.

19:24.597 --> 19:26.292
Oh, Malph, what do you want?

19:26.432 --> 19:28.560
- Three nights in the bed.
- One night.

19:28.701 --> 19:31.398
Hi, my little cupcake.
I'm all yours.

19:31.537 --> 19:32.470
Two nights!

19:32.605 --> 19:33.936
Deal.

19:35.474 --> 19:37.704
Hi, my little cupcake.

19:37.843 --> 19:39.333
Wham?

19:40.713 --> 19:42.238
Wrong number.

19:42.381 --> 19:43.644
All right, Malph, that's it.

19:43.783 --> 19:45.273
Put 'em up.
I've had it with you.

19:45.418 --> 19:47.785
- Come on, put 'em up. Come on.
- If you're gonna threaten me,

19:47.920 --> 19:50.116
-do it from your own side
of the room. -Fine. Fine.

19:50.256 --> 19:52.020
Come on. Come on.
You're over the line, Malph.

19:52.158 --> 19:54.024
- Come on.
- Get your hand back.

19:54.160 --> 19:55.787
Watch the line.
Come on. Come on.

19:55.928 --> 19:57.259
-(knocking)
- It's for me.

19:57.396 --> 19:59.956
- How do you know?
- It's my door.

20:00.099 --> 20:03.865
- Hey, Rich. Come on in.
- Hi, Ralph. Hey, Potsie.

20:04.003 --> 20:07.564
What'd you decide to do, turn
your place into a tennis court?

20:07.707 --> 20:09.004
(chuckles)

20:11.577 --> 20:13.272
We divided the room.

20:13.412 --> 20:15.540
Why'd you do
a stupid thing like that?

20:15.681 --> 20:17.046
Aunt Fanny told us.

20:17.183 --> 20:19.652
Ha-ha-ha-ha.

20:19.785 --> 20:22.049
That woman has a big mouth.

20:22.188 --> 20:24.680
This is my side.
That's what's his name's side.

20:24.824 --> 20:26.189
Hey, Rich...

20:26.325 --> 20:27.952
like a cold drink?

20:28.994 --> 20:30.462
W-Wait a minute, Rich.

20:30.596 --> 20:32.121
Wouldn't you rather have
a hot chocolate?

20:32.264 --> 20:34.198
-(Richie chuckles)
- Yeah, come on, that's...

20:34.333 --> 20:37.359
POTSIE: Hey, Rich, Rich.
Want to go to the bathroom?

20:38.904 --> 20:40.531
Uh, wait a minute,
look, I-l just...

20:40.673 --> 20:42.607
I came here
to tell you guys something.

20:42.742 --> 20:45.211
I can't hear you--
you're not on my side.

20:45.344 --> 20:47.540
All right,
everybody on the line!

20:47.680 --> 20:49.876
- POTSIEIRALPH: Why?
- It's neutral territory.

20:50.015 --> 20:52.279
On the line, right now.
Ralph, Pots, come on.

20:52.418 --> 20:53.886
- RALPH: All right.
- RICHIE: Hurry up.

20:54.019 --> 20:55.953
- POTSIE: Okay, okay.
- Right on the line.

20:56.088 --> 20:57.852
RALPH:
All right, I'm on the line.

20:57.990 --> 20:59.287
Now...

20:59.425 --> 21:01.450
we're all sensible people
here, right?

21:01.594 --> 21:02.686
POTSIE/RALPH:
Right.

21:02.828 --> 21:04.694
You have your differences,
but they can be settled.

21:04.830 --> 21:06.025
- They were settled.
- By Aunt Fanny.

21:06.165 --> 21:07.792
Well, Aunt Fanny--
see, that's what I want

21:07.933 --> 21:09.059
to talk to you about.

21:09.201 --> 21:10.726
- Well?
- Well, uh...

21:10.870 --> 21:13.066
(chuckles): actually,
it's kind of humorous, in a way.

21:13.205 --> 21:14.331
POTSIE:
Ha...

21:14.473 --> 21:15.634
Well, maybe not humorous.

21:15.775 --> 21:19.336
Uh... guys, listen,
life is full of little ironies.

21:19.478 --> 21:22.778
Rich, can you get on with this?
I'm teetering on the line here.

21:27.319 --> 21:30.584
You guys are great,
and working with no net!

21:35.227 --> 21:37.218
Have you told 'em
you're Aunt Fanny yet?

21:41.233 --> 21:43.600
- I was just getting to that,
Fonz. -Good.

21:43.736 --> 21:44.931
What?

21:45.070 --> 21:46.162
You?

21:46.305 --> 21:48.205
You're Aunt Fanny?

21:48.340 --> 21:50.570
Look, I'm-I'm sorry,
I know I was wrong.

21:50.709 --> 21:52.370
Wrrrr...

21:52.511 --> 21:54.809
RICHIE: And I didn't mean
to give out bad advice.

21:54.947 --> 21:56.210
FONZIE:
Didn't mean it.

21:56.348 --> 21:58.612
- But I was trying to impress
my editor. -Impress his editor.

21:58.751 --> 22:01.152
Oh, man. Should've minded
your own business, Rich.

22:01.287 --> 22:02.311
Really.

22:02.454 --> 22:05.014
- Really.
- I know that. I know.

22:05.157 --> 22:07.125
Think it's been easy for me?
It hasn't.

22:07.259 --> 22:09.159
I'll tell you one thing,
from now on,

22:09.295 --> 22:12.321
